PROBLEM: 'What is the value of '\[3+\frac{1}{3+\frac{1}{3+\frac13}}?\]'\n'$\textbf{(A)}\ \frac{31}{10}\qquad\textbf{(B)}\ \frac{49}{15}\qquad\textbf{(C)}\ \frac{33}{10}\qquad\textbf{(D)}\ \frac{109}{33}\qquad\textbf{(E)}\ \frac{15}{4}$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{31}{10}
[B]: \frac{49}{15}
[C]: \frac{33}{10}
[D]: \frac{109}{33}
[E]: \frac{15}{4}

PROBLEM: 'In some countries, automobile fuel efficiency is measured in liters per '$100$' kilometers while other countries use miles per gallon. Suppose that 1 kilometer equals '$m$' miles, and '$1$' gallon equals '$l$' liters. Which of the following gives the fuel efficiency in liters per '$100$' kilometers for a car that gets '$x$' miles per gallon?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{x}{100lm}
[B]: \frac{xlm}{100}
[C]: \frac{lm}{100x}
[D]: \frac{100}{xlm}
[E]: \frac{100lm}{x}

PROBLEM: 'Square '$ABCD$' has side length '$1$'. Points '$P$', '$Q$', '$R$', and '$S$' each lie on a side of '$ABCD$' such that '$APQCRS$' is an equilateral convex hexagon with side length '$s$'. What is '$s$'?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{\sqrt{2}}{3}
[B]: \frac{1}{2}
[C]: 2 - \sqrt{2}
[D]: 1 - \frac{\sqrt{2}}{4}
[E]: \frac{2}{3}

PROBLEM: 'The roots of the polynomial '$10x^3 - 39x^2 + 29x - 6$' are the height, length, and width of a rectangular box (right rectangular prism). A new rectangular box is formed by lengthening each edge of the original box by '$2$'\nunits. What is the volume of the new box?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{24}{5}
[B]: \frac{42}{5}
[C]: \frac{81}{5}
[D]: 30
[E]: 48

PROBLEM: 'Isosceles trapezoid '$ABCD$' has parallel sides '$\overline{AD}$' and '$\overline{BC},$' with '$BC < AD$' and '$AB = CD.$' There is a point '$P$' in the plane such that '$PA=1, PB=2, PC=3,$' and '$PD=4.$' What is '$\tfrac{BC}{AD}?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{1}{4}
[B]: \frac{1}{3}
[C]: \frac{1}{2}
[D]: \frac{2}{3}
[E]: \frac{3}{4}
